The men, aged 32 and 39, were charged with murder and attempted murder and were expected to appear in court in due course. Police spokesperson Lieutenant-Colonel Thulani Zwane said a group of heavily armed men entered the shopping complex on Friday and opened fire on security guards. Five people died at the scene and a sixth person died in hospital a few days later. â€œThe men fled with an undisclosed amount of money. Among the victims who died are two security guards and a member of the public who was sitting in his vehicle," Zwane said. The supermarket owners were not injured during the robbery, he said. The murder, attempted murder and robbery dockets were opened at Mthunzini police station. Daily News